  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large pot over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-chicken-with-creamy-apple-sage-lentils/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, grate the <strong>apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (skin on)</p><p>Strip the <strong>sage leaves</strong> from their stems (discard the stems!) and roughly chop <strong>half </strong>of the leaves finely (keep the rest whole!)</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>in<strong> </strong>450ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-chicken-with-creamy-apple-sage-lentils/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the<strong> grated apple</strong>, <strong>chopped sage</strong> (save the whole leaves for later!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pot and cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-chicken-with-creamy-apple-sage-lentils/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>puy-style lentils</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>rinsed lentils </strong>to the pot along with the<strong> stock</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce to medium-low and cook for 30-35 min or until tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-chicken-with-creamy-apple-sage-lentils/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the lentils are cooking, trim the <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Season the <strong>chicken breast portions </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-chicken-with-creamy-apple-sage-lentils/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken breasts</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p><p>Once golden, reduce the heat to medium and add a small splash of<strong> water</strong> to the pan, then cover with a lid</p><p>Increase the heat to medium high and cook for an initial 5 min</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-chicken-with-creamy-apple-sage-lentils/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 5 min, remove the lid and add the <strong>trimmed green beans </strong>and <strong>remaining sage leaves </strong>to the pan, then cook, uncovered, for 5-7 min further or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!), the beans are tender, and the sage is crisp</p><p>Once the lentils are tender, add the <strong>soft cheese</strong> to the pot, season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> stir to combine – these are your <strong>creamy apple & sage lentils</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-chicken-with-creamy-apple-sage-lentils/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy apple & sage lentils </strong>in wide bowls topped with the <strong>pan-fried</strong> <strong>chicken</strong>, <strong>green beans </strong>and <strong>crispy sage leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
